Last update: 090925. Yang Yu (Hanchuan Peng lab)

Bio-Formats Plugin 

0. Preparation

download boost (http://www.boost.org, recommend version 1.41.0 or higher) and make install boost
download cmake (http://www.cmake.org/cmake/resources/software.html) and make install cmake
# windows
download ant (http://ant.apache.org)

1. Downloading Bio-Formats

svn co https://skyking.microscopy.wisc.edu/svn/java/trunk loci
svn co https://jace.svn.sourceforge.net/svnroot/jace/trunk jace 

# svn version loci 5698 jace 35

2. Compiling Bio-Formats

cd loci
ant tools
cd components/native/bf-cpp
ant -Djace.home=/Users/yuy/work/jace

#note that the last command must be absolute path, according to yuy
#Windows: ant -Djace.home=C:/jace using '/' instead of '\'. Set JAVA_HOME make ant find javac.

# for windows x64 compiling bf-cpp change the line of build.properties
cmake.generator.windows = Visual Studio 9 2008 Win64

3. Set the Build Results to your path

# libjace.so / libjace.jnilib / jace.dll Jace shared library
# libbfjace.so / libbfjace.dylib / bfjace.dll Bio-Formats C++ bindings
# jace-runtime.jar  Jace Java classes needed at runtime
# loci_tools.jar  Bio-Formats Java library needed at runtime 

# above libs could be found at /loci/components/native/bf-cpp/build
# bio-formats.jar at /loci/artifacts


Compilation:

# Example .pro file suppose corresponding libs copied to ../bioformat_lib/lib (32-bit) or ../bioformat_lib/lib64 (64-bit)
# and corresponding header files (bio-formats.h, jace.h, loci-common.h and jace) copied to ../bioformat_lib/include 

Compilation of bioformat_ex (Readimage_bioformat) needs to copy dependent libraries to V3D working directory.
Compiling 64-bit version loci needs java 6 (1.6.0) or higher.

# note in windows: dependent libboost will be boost_date_time and boost_thread


September 22, 2009
